The paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of actor-critic algorithms and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.RO (Robotics). The focus on cooperative tasks and joint actions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the consideration of constraints and penalty functions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
